          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You've always been a tinkerer.  You won the engineering prize at Groton your senior year and went straight to MIT.  There your love of pranks - kept somewhat in check at Groton by vigilant dorm faculty and a lingering fear of parental disapproval - went wild.   Sabotaging the Harvard-Yale game your freshman year won you great acclaim.  But as you got older, and the pressure of performing at a place like MIT got higher, your pranks got darker, more nasty, more dangerous.    Junior year first semester finals was the breaking point, when you rigged that bunsen burner.  You didn't expect the idiots would mis-measure the formula!   But the hospitalizations and that death ended your career there.  You ended up kicking around a bunch of odd jobs, becoming increasingly isolated from other people.  Then a trip up to Montreal led you to meet some people who shared your macabre view on the world and well...    You really feel you've found your people with your current pack.  The traps you craft to deal with the beasties you hunt are always appreciated. They indulge you in your particular interests and in return you make sure there are nasty surprises waiting for any Lupine unlucky enough to fall into your sights."
        ],
