          "Your pack ductus - you think sometimes he can be a bit rash, but you're never going to doubt his courage."
        ],
        [
          "Harry/Harriet Lowell",
          "Your pack abbot.  They can be a little goofy sometimes.  Okay, it's more of a default setting.  But nobody takes care of the group better.  And it sure is handy to have somebody around who can deal with the mortals.  And really, Technicolor Dreamboat really is kinda clever.  Charlie and Spencer roll their eyes sometimes, but you and Harry/Harriet love your puns..."
        ],
        [
          "Charlie Prescott",
          "They can be a snot sometimes, but at the end of they day, they're loyal and driven to get the job done.  Maybe the one of your packmates who best appreciates your more cerebral approach to the hunt."
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Starting Goals",
          "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        ],
        [
          "All your time hunting the changing breeds has had its consequences.  They know you and they're after you, too.  You've all had some close calls.  So you developed an ignobilis ritae to deal with it.  Touch the Wyld lets the pack become aware fo the presence of werecreatures.  You can use this to eliminate the DT cost of the Hunted flaw for one pack member (must be determined beforehand).  Or you can alternately use it to find a were-beast to hunt.   The foucs of the ritae is a were-jaguar pelt (very rare!).  But it must be recharged by wrapping it in the still warm body of your most recent kill. The pelt can hold a \"charge\" for up to three months.  But,  if you go three months without recharging the ritual focus or using the charge currently in it, it will disintegrate.   You don't want to think about the trouble of making a new one.  And it needs recharging.  Like, right away."
        ],
        [
          "You are very proud of this ritual, but you know it could be improved.   To accomplish that, you need access to arcane resources.  The Tremere had a chantry here in San Diego that might have materials useful to your research.   See about gaining access.  Are there others in the city also interested in the Chantry?  Perhaps you could pool your efforts!"
        ],
        [
          "Hunting is a precise business that requires tremendous preparation to be successful.   You need to gather intelligence about the local area before you can even think of starting a hunt.  Be sure to seek out those in San Diego with more local knowledge who migth be able to offer you such information."
        ],
